  "instructions": [
    "Chop the Korean Seaweed into small pieces.",
    "Heat Sunflower Oil in a pan over medium heat. Add chopped seaweed and sprinkle with salt and black pepper.",
    "Stir occasionally for about 2 minutes until seaweed starts to turn golden brown.",
    "Add lemon juice and stir well. The seaweed should be moistened evenly, achieving the desired texture of being sweet yet crispy.",
    "Garnish with fresh mint leaves before serving."
